# Blade and Views

Match the default UI is React; use Blade only when needed (e.g. shell, login, error). When using Blade, match reference app’s view layout and patterns.

## Structure

- **Layout**: Main views `@extends('app')` and use `@section('content')`.
- **Path**: `resources/views/components/contents/{resource}/` for a resource:
  - `{resource}Form.blade.php` (create), `{resource}Edit.blade.php`, `{resource}Show.blade.php`
  - `{resource}List.blade.php` (list page), `tables/{resource}ListTable.blade.php` (AJAX table partial)
- **Partials**: Reuse `components/partials/` (e.g. `modal`, `documents-section`, `notes-section`, `breadcrumb`, `search-bar`) via `<x-partials.name />`.

## Naming

- Blade file names in **camelCase** for the resource: `materialAssignmentForm.blade.php`, `materialAssignmentShow.blade.php`.

## Forms and links

- Use `route('route_name')` or `route('route_name', $model)` for actions and links.
- Use `old('field_name', $model->field ?? '')` to repopulate inputs on validation errors.
- Always `@csrf` in forms.

## Validation errors

- Show errors in Catalan. Example:

```blade
@if ($errors->any())
    <div class="alert alert-error ...">
        <h3 class="...">Hi ha errors en el formulari:</h3>
        <ul>@foreach ($errors->all() as $error)<li>{{ $error }}</li>@endforeach</ul>
    </div>
@endif
```

## Styling in views

- Use **Tailwind** utility classes and **daisyUI** component classes. See `.cursor/rules/tailwind.mdc` and `.cursor/rules/daisyui.mdc` for correct class names and patterns.

## Copy

- All user-visible text (labels, buttons, titles, messages) must be in **Catalan**, as per project standards.
